modules.description: Processes OCaml source files with macro expansion and file inclusion, supporting inline definitions and conditional compilation. Operates on OCaml syntax trees and source code strings, enabling dynamic code generation. Used to simplify repetitive code patterns and manage platform-specific implementations.

Provides rules for integrating cppo preprocessing into Ocamlbuild, applying transformations to files with specified extensions. Works with Ocamlbuild's build rules and plugin hooks. Enables conditional compilation and macro expansion in OCaml source files during the build process.
